# Gander — Project Goals

Location-based dating app. Stack: **Next.js 16 (App Router)**, **TypeScript**, **Supabase Auth + Postgres**, **Tailwind CSS**. Dev server runs on **port 3001**.

## Goal 1 (current): Login, Auth & Profile

Complete the sign-up/sign-in flow, session protection, and a real user profile page before building discovery, location, or matching features.

### Done

- `/` — login page with email/password sign-in and create-account toggle (`components/login-form.tsx`)
- Supabase clients: `lib/supabase/client.ts`, `lib/supabase/server.ts`
- Session + route protection via `proxy.ts` → `lib/supabase/session.ts`
  - Unauthenticated users on `/app/*` → redirect to `/`
  - Authenticated users on `/` → redirect to `/app`
- Auth callback: `app/auth/callback/route.ts` (email confirmation / OAuth code exchange)
- `/app/profile` — basic stub (email, member since, sign out)
- App shell with bottom tab nav: Home Feed + Profile (`components/app-nav.tsx`)

### Remaining for Goal 1

#### 1. Finish auth hardening

- [ ] Confirm email flow works end-to-end (sign up → confirm → sign in)
- [ ] Add `lib/supabase/admin.ts` (service-role, server-only) when server-side profile ops need it
- [ ] Populate `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in `.env.local` (never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`)
- [ ] Link Supabase CLI: `npx supabase login` + `npx supabase link --project-ref vyaztisfdtpxmqdyfqln`
- [ ] Friendly auth error messages — never leak raw Supabase/Postgres errors to UI

#### 2. Apply profiles schema

- [ ] Add migration `supabase/migrations/dating_app_schema_v2_slim.sql` and run `npx supabase db push`
- [ ] Generate types: `npx supabase gen types typescript --linked > lib/database.types.ts`
- [ ] Create private `profile-photos` storage bucket with user-scoped policies

Profile fields (slim v2):

| Field | Column | Rules |
|---|---|---|
| Username | `username` (citext) | `^[a-z0-9_]{3,20}$`, check via `username_available()` RPC |
| Name | `display_name` | 1–30 chars |
| Age | `date_of_birth` | 18+ enforced by DB; DOB never exposed to other users |
| Bio | `bio` | ≤ 500 chars |
| Photo | `photo_path` | private bucket, served via signed URLs only |

#### 3. Data layer

Create `lib/data/profiles.ts` with typed helpers:

- `checkUsernameAvailable(username)` → `username_available` RPC
- `createProfile({ username, displayName, dateOfBirth, bio? })`
- `updateProfile(patch)` — own row only
- `uploadProfilePhoto(file)` — jpeg/png/webp, ≤ 5 MB, path `{uid}/avatar.{ext}`
- `getSignedPhotoUrl(photoPath)` — server-side, ~60 min TTL

#### 4. Onboarding + profile UI

- [ ] `/onboarding` — multi-step: username (debounced availability) → name + DOB → bio → photo
- [ ] Redirect new users without a `profiles` row to `/onboarding` (in `proxy.ts` or page guard)
- [ ] Upgrade `/app/profile` to show and edit: username, display name, bio, photo preview
- [ ] Keep sign out on profile page (`components/sign-out-button.tsx`)

#### 5. Goal 1 verification

- [ ] New user: sign up → onboarding → lands on `/app` with profile complete
- [ ] Returning user: sign in → `/app` (skip onboarding if profile exists)
- [ ] Protected routes reject unauthenticated access
- [ ] Username collision and under-18 DOB return friendly errors
- [ ] Profile photo upload rejects wrong type/size before upload

## Conventions

- TypeScript strict; no `any` in data layer
- Match existing UI: rose/zinc palette, rounded-xl cards, bottom tab nav
- Privacy: raw lat/lng never reach the client (relevant for later goals, not Goal 1)
- Service role key: server-only imports (`lib/supabase/admin.ts`, route handlers, server actions)
- Do not redesign the migration SQL — private schema + RPC pattern is intentional

## Key paths

```
app/page.tsx              → login
app/app/page.tsx          → home feed (done, out of Goal 1 scope)
app/app/profile/page.tsx  → profile (expand in Goal 1)
app/onboarding/           → create (Goal 1)
proxy.ts                  → auth redirects
components/login-form.tsx
lib/supabase/
lib/data/profiles.ts      → create (Goal 1)
```

